Hi @jywu-msft  
I would like to add some information:

Using the SDK to build the hello.cpp successfully with below code:

> #include <assert.h>
> #include "onnxruntime_c_api.h"
> #include <stdlib.h>
> #include <stdio.h>
> #include <vector>
> #include <map>
> #include <fstream>
> #define STB_IMAGE_IMPLEMENTATION
> #include "stb_image.h"
> #include <stdio.h>
> int main() {
>     printf("Hello, world!\n");
>     return 0;
> }

but when I insert below line to code, it will lead to the error in above post.
> const OrtApi* g_ort = OrtGetApiBase()->GetApi(ORT_API_VERSION);

i think the issue is datetime_transformer.cc.o has a dependency on libautoml_featurizers.a which it doesn't look like you built. see: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/v1.0.0/cmake/onnxruntime_automl_featurizers.cmake#L13

but for your purposes (tinyyolov2) you don't need featurizers at all.
so you shouldn't build datetime_transformer.cc etc. 

in other words,
when building libonnxruntime_providers.a  , make sure you don't include any source files from 
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/tree/v1.0.0/onnxruntime/automl_ops

Hi @jywu-msft 

Thank you very much for your support.
As your comment, I just found that my Makefile lack of  libautoml_featurizers.a
after add line **-lautoml_featurizers** to Makefile, the compiling was built successfully.

so Thank again for your support.  You are so handsome!
